<html> 
<head>
<title>Arlen Specter: Political Philosophy</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/paper2.jpg">
<center>
<h2>Arlen Specter: Political Philosophy</h2> <P>
</center>
I believe the core of the Republican Party, and the essence of American greatness, is respect for
freedom--freedom of the mind as well as the marketplace.  Reverence for the principle of human
freedom must establish the relationship between government and individuals--a relationship that
must be defined by the values of economic conservatism and social libertarianism.<P>
Economic conservatism means a recognition:  that prosperity and opportunity are the products of
free markets, not government bureaucracies or state welfare programs;  that economic growth
comes form low taxes and less government regulation;  and that we cannot continue to mortgage
our children's future with national debt.<P>
Social libertarianism means a recognition:  that human freedom must be spiritual as well as
economic; that our government must respect, absolutely and equally, the religious beliefs of all
Americans; and that the reproductive choices of American women are not a matter for
government intrusion.<P>
The principles of economic conservatism and social libertarianism mean limited government, but
not uncaring or do nothing government.  Consistent with these principles, government does have
a role to play in fighting crime, in expanding access to health care, in improving education and in
promoting economic opportunity--a role that government must play in partnership with the
values established in American homes, communities and places of worship.<P>
America's unique position in the world as its bastion of peace and beacon of freedom demands
the preservation of our nation as a self-reliant economic and military power second to none.<P>
<br>
<a href="http://BizServe.com/Specter">Go to the Arlen Specter Home Page</a><br>
<a href="specbio.html">Arlen Specter Biography</a><br>
<a href="contents.html">Introduction</a>
</body>
</html>
